            <a href="/author-jef-dewitt">
            <h4 class="text-dark mb-0"> Jef DeWitt </h4>
            <small class="d-inline-block mt-1 mb-3 font-weight-normal">(View Posts)</small>
            <div class="excerpt">By my mid-thirties I was living in active addiction, divorced, and unemployed. I was a mess. And it was a profound wake up call.</div>
            <div class="excerpt">I began rebuilding my life after a simple realization; that living in addiction is incredibly hard work. I found hope in that. Because I recognized that if I applied that same ethic to educating and improving myself, it gave me a chance.</div>
            <div class="excerpt">Through my recovery and years in therapy, I got a humbling education in self-discipline, emotional intelligence, and practical lessons in healthy relationships. I humbly share the amalgamation of all my research and experimentation in an honest effort to help heal; myself and others.</div>
